editedProxies

public final java.util.Map<SimpleProxyId<?>,AutoBean<? extends BaseProxy>> editedProxies
A map of all EntityProxies that the RequestContext has interacted with. Objects are placed into this map by being returned from AbstractRequestContext.create(java.lang.Class), passed into AbstractRequestContext.edit(T), or used as an invocation argument.

returnedProxies

public final java.util.Map<SimpleProxyId<?>,AutoBean<?>> returnedProxies
A map that contains the canonical instance of an entity to return in the return graph, since this is built from scratch.

requestFactory

public final AbstractRequestFactory requestFactory

syntheticIds

public final java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,SimpleProxyId<?>> syntheticIds
A map that allows us to handle the case where the server has sent back an unpersisted entity. Because we assume that the server is stateless, the client will need to swap out the request-local ids with a regular client-allocated id.
